Kobe Bryant Leads West to 148-143 NBA All-Star Game Win in Los Angeles

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-02-21T04:31:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/kobe-bryant-leads-west-to-148-143-nba-all-star-game-win-in-los-angeles.html
  Kobe Bryant  scored 37 points on his
home court to lead the Western Conference to a 148-143 win over
the East in the National Basketball Association All-Star Game in
Los Angeles.   The Lakersâ€™ Bryant, who was pursuing a record-tying fourth
All-Star Most Valuable Player award, led all scorers and added
14 rebounds at the Staples Center.   Bryant scored 11 points in the first quarter to help the
West build a 37-27 lead. The West led by as many as 17 points in
the fourth quarter before holding off a late rally by the East,
who pulled within 142-140 with 1:12 left.    LeBron James  of the Miami Heat led the Eastern Conference
with 29 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists.  Michael Jordan  had
the only other triple-double in an All-Star Game in 1997.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
